id: pm-9k90
title: "MCP tool profiles: core/standard/full/custom tiers with an allowlist override, so 28 tools are the maximum surface, not the default"
description: "Tier the MCP tool surface: core (~10 tools: pm_next, pm_context, pm_search, pm_get, pm_create, pm_claim, pm_update, pm_close, pm_plan, pm_validate), standard (adds workflow+evidence: pm_append, pm_files, pm_docs, pm_notes, pm_learnings, pm_deps, pm_test, pm_health, pm_profile, pm_config), full (all narrow tools + pm_run), custom (env/config allowlist e.g. PM_MCP_TOOLS=pm_next,pm_context,...). pm_run stays a fallback for advanced/low-frequency operations, never the first tool an agent sees. Distinct new feature — does NOT reopen the dispositioned pm-mpbb DX lever list (a-d)."
type: Feature
status: open
priority: 2
tags[4]: agents,ergonomics,mcp,token-surface
created_at: "2026-07-13T09:32:01.899Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-16T05:45:15.776Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 480
acceptance_criteria: "Profile selection via MCP server config/env with core as a deliberate product decision for the default; tools/list payload for core measured via scripts/measure-agent-token-surface.mjs and published (baseline: 28 tools = 32979 B ~= 8.2k tokens per pm-a22j); custom allowlist validated against known tool names with clear errors; profiles documented in registry metadata and plugin docs; contract/drift gates cover per-profile tool sets; existing integration suites pass under every profile"
parent: pm-mpbb
risk: low
confidence: high
dependencies[2]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
  pm-wjfa,related,"2026-07-13T09:32:01.899Z",null,null
