notes[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-13T09:32:19.589Z",maintainer-agent,"Rationale evidence: June 2026 tool-selection study (arxiv 2606.30317) found substantial accuracy degradation as available tool count grows (threshold varies by model); Task Master independently ships core/standard/full MCP tiers with explicit token budgets for the same reason. Pair with MCP resources+prompts (owned by pm-z3ez) so stable reference context does not need to be a tool. Selection quality is an agent-acquisition lever, not just a token saving — a smaller, sharper surface makes agents pick pm tools correctly more often."
  "2026-07-15T19:27:28.263Z",maintainer-agent,"Re-measurement 2026-07-15 (review pass #89, scripts/measure-agent-token-surface.mjs): MCP tools/list 33,314 B / 8,329 tokens / 28 tools — up from the pm-a22j baseline 32,979 B (2026-07-11). Every session with the MCP server attached pays ~8.3k tokens before the first call, and each new tool/flag grows it; the core/standard/full profile tiers this item owns are the structural fix. Companion figure: full-format single-item surface is 539,946 B (~135k tokens) vs summary_json 4,426 B — the 122x spread shows how much the profile/format choices matter for agent context budgets."
body: ""
